The '''Emblem Trader''' is a mysterious merchant who runs the [[Bounty Hunter Shop]]. His store sells various cosmetic items, such as [[abyssal whip]] and [[dark bow]] recolours, and useful items such as [[Ancient Magicks]] teleport tablets.

He can [[skull (status)|skull]] the player should they ask him to, and limit potential Bounty Hunter targets to those below level 10 [[Wilderness]] only.

He also wanders the [[Revenant Caves]] in search of ancient artefacts. Players can give him [[ancient artefacts]] (either [[noted]] or un-noted) to receive a large amount of [[coins]]. However, he will only accept them on the current official [[Bounty Hunter]] world (either world 318 or 319, depending on the rotation) and on a [[Shattered Relics League]] world. This trader cannot open the Bounty Hunter shop, as he states that it is too dangerous to do so.

As an alternative to taking [[Coins]] or an [[Antique emblem]] into the [[Bounty Hunter]] [[Minigame]], which is necessary to get a Target, players may use the Emblem Trader's Coffer to deposit the required amount of [[Coins]] up to a maximum of {{NoCoins|2,000,000}} coins.

==Mysterious emblems==
Players can purchase [[mysterious emblem]]s from the Emblem Trader; there are five tiers of emblem with increasing values. Once a mysterious emblem is purchased, players can upgrade the emblem or sell it back to the [[Emblem Trader]] for the same amount of coins. Players cannot buy a tier 5 emblem; they are obtainable only by upgrading a tier 4 emblem.

